Harpalus sp. Likely H. erraticus. Large and pale. Very distinct process at subapical sinuation of elytra. Pronotum narrower in rear with straight posterior edge. Pronotum is slightly rounded with fine punctation at edges.
3-4mm long. Similar to Syntomus americanus. Narrow waists between elytra pronotum and head. Black.
Cymindis sp. Larger than Cymindis interior. Elytra have strong sinuation. Pronotum widest at anterior edge.
3-4mm long. Similar to Syntomus americanus. Narrow waists between elytra pronotum and head. Black.
Harpalus sp. Similar to HARDES. One puncuated fovea on each side of pronotum. Corresponding dents on elytra. Sharp angles of anterior pronotum. Arched pronotum. Nuptial pads on forelimbs.
Calathus sp. Possibly C. opaculus. Pronotum nearly square. Pronotum and elytra pale at margins. Elytra dull with heavy microsculpture.
